annotationA: Regulator of chromosome condensation 1 (Rcc1) is the guanine-nucleotide exchange factor for Ran. It promotes the nucleo-cytoplasmic shuttling of specific proteins and regulates chromatin condensation. Rcc1 roles include cell proliferation, cell survival, apoptosis, epigenetic regulation, and neuronal specification
annotationB: Ran GTPase-activating protein; GTPase activator for the nuclear Ras-related regulatory protein Ran, converting it to the putatively inactive GDP-bound state (By similarity). Trans-acting factor necessary for meiotic distortion. Distortion is only seen in individuals that carry the RanGAP tandem duplication and express a RanGAP truncated protein. Binding of truncated RanGAP product to the Responder(RSP) locus initiates events that lead to sperm dysfunction
